SIMPLE: glaciate
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Glaciate
<hw>Gla"ci*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>glaciatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>glaciare</ets> to freeze, fr.
<ets>glacies</ets> ice.]</ety> <def>To turn to ice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glaciate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Glaciate
<hw>Gla"ci*ate</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To convert into,
or cover with, ice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>To produce glacial effects upon,
as in the scoring of rocks, transportation of loose material,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Glaciated rocks</b></col>, <cd>rocks whose surfaces have
been smoothed, furrowed, or striated, by the action of
ice.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glaciation</ent>⟦br⟧
